The paper deals with distributed algorithms for constructing routing schemes in a network, which falls under the category of Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The algorithm is designed for a weighted undirected graph, which is a common topic in Network Information Theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the size of routing tables and labels, which are related to Data Structures (cs.DS). The paper uses mathematical analysis to derive the running time and stretch of the routing scheme, which is related to the field of Theoretical Computer Science (cs.TH). Finally, the paper discusses the state-of-the-art for routing schemes, which is related to Algorithmic Theory (cs.AL).
